@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-primary mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>This Privacy Policy outlines how the <strong>Sales Forecasting Dashboard</strong> application collects, uses, and protects any information you provide while using this site.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Sales Data:</strong> Uploaded sales records (dates and amounts) are stored in a secure SQL Server database.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Logs:</strong> We may collect anonymized data for analytics purposes such as usage frequency and page visits.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">2. How We Use Your Data</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>To generate accurate sales forecasts using ML.NET time series models.</li>
        <li>To help improve application performance and functionality.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">3. Data Protection</h4>
    <p>We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. All data is stored securely, and access is restricted to authorized personnel only.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">4. Cookies</h4>
    <p>This site may use basic cookies for functionality and analytics. You may disable cookies in your browser settings.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-4">5. Your Control</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>You can request the deletion of uploaded data by contacting the site administrator.</li>
        <li>No personal identifiable information is required or stored by default.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4">6. Changes to This Policy</h4>
    <p>We may update this privacy policy periodically. Please check this page occasionally to ensure you are comfortable with any changes.</p>

    <p class="mt-4">If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, please contact us through the application support page.</p>
</div>
